**[1862, 01-21] Ms.A.9.2.31.1**

RDW to [AWW?]

She is now in “a white heat of anti British enthusiasm. I don’t think we
are as bad or that you are as good as you suppose. Most likely there
have been faults on both sides, plenty of ignorance & mutual
misapprehension in England & in America. … As matters now stand it seems
difficult to say a word without doing mischief, even with the very best
& most upright intentions. I am truly sorry for it.”


